The Kisutu today sentenced National Chairman with Chadema and eight other senior party officials to a total of 350m/- fine or go to jail for 60 months after being convicted of 12 seditious counts against them. Senior Resident Magistrate Thomas Simba passed such sentence after the prosecution proved the charges against them beyond reasonable doubt. Other convicts are former partyâ€™s Secretary General Vicent Mashinji, John Mnyika, the newly elected Secretary General and Salum Mwalimu, who is Deputy Secretary General (Zanzibar). Others are Peter Msigwa (Member of Parliament (MP) for Iringa Urban, Halima Mdee, the MP for Kawe, John Heche, the MP for Tarime Rural and Ester Bulaya, who is MP for Bunda Urban as well as the MP for Tarime Urban, Ester Matiko.